`mkbtimg' and `rdbtimg' create boot images (including the header) and
dump the header contents of an existing boot image, respectively. 

Example usage:
    ./mkbtimg histar_boot 2048 0x10000100 0x10010000:../histar/obj.arm/boot/bimage.init 0x11000000:fake_ramdisk   
    ./rdbtimg histar_boot
    fastboot flash boot histar_boot

`fastboot' is an HTC binary for flashing nand partitions from the device
firmware

NB: For some reason, the device interprets 0x10000100 as 0x80000100.
NB: A ramdisk must always be present, though a secondary loader is optional. I
    just use a single page (2048byte) zero block and ignore it.
